# simplbooks — credentials (copy to $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/simplbooks/credentials.env,
# default ~/.config/simplbooks/credentials.env, and fill).
# For the SESSION keys this is the tier-2 (user config) source; their cascade is
# two-tier — THIS user config > process env (no flags / project .env; see
# deviations.md). The non-secret ACCOUNT-CONFIG keys use the full cascade:
#   flag > project .env(.local) > THIS user config > process env
# so a consuming project can set them in its own .env instead of here.
# Values are literal to end-of-line — keep comments on their own lines.
# PUBLIC REPO: never commit real values. Leave blank here; fill only the copy.

# ── Login (primary auth path: auto-login + expiry recovery) ───────────────────
# Email + password for the SimpleBooks account. With both present the CLI
# re-authenticates itself when the session expires. A new IP/device triggers a
# PIN gate: run `simplbooks login`, then `simplbooks login --pin <code>` with the
# 6-digit code SimpleBooks emails. Never pass on argv.
SIMPLBOOKS_EMAIL=
SIMPLBOOKS_PASSWORD=

# ── Session (written by `simplbooks login` / `simplbooks refresh`) ────────────
# The live login: a session cookie and the 32-char account hash. You normally do
# NOT fill these by hand — `login`/`refresh` persist them here. The cookie is
# auth material; never commit it.
SIMPLBOOKS_COOKIE=
SIMPLBOOKS_ACCOUNT=

# ── Account config (write paths only) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# No id is baked into the tool. Reads need none of these. VAT types, their rates,
# and the default income account are read LIVE from SimpleBooks per invoice
# (`simplbooks invoices meta` / `expenses meta`); the issuer (creator) is read
# from the form as the logged-in user. A consuming project may set these in its
# own .env instead of here.

# Invoice issuer name — `invoices create` needs it (or pass --worker). No default.
SIMPLBOOKS_WORKER=

# Own bank account row id shown on invoices — `invoices create` (or --bank-account).
# Discover with `simplbooks accounts list cashbook`.
# SIMPLBOOKS_BANK_ACCOUNT=

# Bank integration target for `expenses send-payment` (or --target).
# SIMPLBOOKS_BANK_TARGET=

# OPTIONAL income-account override, per sales regime. The income account defaults
# to the live vat_types value; set a key only for a regime whose revenue books to
# a different chart row than SimpleBooks' default (e.g. EU/export → a 0% revenue
# account). Discover ids with `simplbooks accounts list chart`.
# SIMPLBOOKS_INCOMEACCT_EE_DOMESTIC=
# SIMPLBOOKS_INCOMEACCT_EU_REVERSE=
# SIMPLBOOKS_INCOMEACCT_NON_EU=

# Optional invoice footer line (a courtesy default ships built in).
# SIMPLBOOKS_INVOICE_FOOTER=
